<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="948" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d948">
                        <head>[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-31"><hi rend="italic">May 31,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The fort overlooking Managua blew up this afternoon; between 60 and 70 of
                            the garrison killed. Diaz and Mena believe it is part of the Liberal
                            plot, and a number of arrests have been made.</p>
                        <p>President Beltrán of Honduras wires Nicaraguan Government that the
                            filibuster <hi rend="italic">Eureka</hi> left Salina Cruz May 30 with
                            cargo of arms, ostensibly for Amapala. I have informed legation in
                            Salvador.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Northcott.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
